gressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff5ce6884-dc5d-480d-99fe-a20642903a46_900x642.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://www.ft.com/content/c77fefa3-7f47-429b-8149-50aa60f39498">ft</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>实际上，中国公司<a href="https://www.orfonline.org/research/to-stay-or-to-go-decoding-chinese-enterprises-india-dilemma">也在印度投资，尽管</a>从长远来看，这将有助于印度成为中国的经济竞争对手。最终，个人激励通常胜过民族主义担忧。</p><p>即使您忽略了该问题的国家安全方面，您也应该同意，将中国生产到印度，越南，印度尼西亚等的公司是一件非常好的事情。这些国家比中国贫穷得多，这意味着它们比中国更需要增长： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F97a4f203-5636-465c-9939-931e3864fd08_1020x717.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F97a4f203-5636-465c-9939-931e3864fd08_1020x717.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F97a4f203-5636-465c-9939-931e3864fd08_1020x717.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F97a4f203-5636-465c-9939-931e3864fd08_1020x717.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F97a4f203-5636-465c-9939-931e3864fd08_1020x717.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F97a4f203-5636-465c-9939-931e3864fd08_1020x717.png" width="688" height="483.6235294117647" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/97a4f203-5636-465c-9939-931e3864fd08_1020x717.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:717,&quot;width&quot;:1020,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:688,&quot;bytes&quot;:113313,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F97a4f203-5636-465c-9939-931e3864fd08_1020x717.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F97a4f203-5636-465c-9939-931e3864fd08_1020x717.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F97a4f203-5636-465c-9939-931e3864fd08_1020x717.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F97a4f203-5636-465c-9939-931e3864fd08_1020x717.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>归根结底，西方和中国企业将工厂迁往新一轮发展中国家，只是旧的<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flying_geese_paradigm">“雁行论”发展论</a>的又一例证。但是在这种情况下，鹅需要额外的推动力才能使他们离开中国。关税提供了这种推动力，全球穷人可能因此受益匪浅。</p><h4> 4. 租金管制有实际成本</h4><p>根据我的观察，租房者，以及像 YIMBY 这样致力于让租房者生活更轻松的人，都对租金管制的想法非常感兴趣。毕竟，造成租房者立即痛苦的事情是……好吧，租金增加。因此，想要<em>禁止痛苦的事情</em>，让眼前的痛苦消失，这是可以理解的。</p><p>人们普遍认为，租金管制可能会对租房者产生一些负面的<em>长期</em>后果——这项政策可能只是暂时的拐杖，让未来的情况变得更糟。但是现在是现在，明天是明天，总是很想<a href="https://x.com/alfred_twu/status/1800057440903581939">找到理由说服自己</a>，短期福利无需成本。</p><p>但现实是，长期成本通常是存在的。康斯坦丁·霍洛迪林 (Konstantin Kholodilin) 对租金管制研究进行了<a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1051137724000020?via%3Dihub">大量新文献综述</a>—— <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/180Pop64kR-RRSVx_jj_2wYc8J_C-WfWCL80NEePrLNY/edit?gid=0#gid=0">这是他引用的所有研究的电子表格</a>——他得出的结论是，其缺点是非常真实的：</p><blockquote><p>租金控制是否有用，还是造成比公用事业更大的损害？…这项研究回顾了大型经验文献……在减慢为控制所支付的住宅的租金增长方面，租金控制似乎非常有效。但是，这项政策也导致了影响整个社会的广泛不利影响……</p><p> [a]通常在此研究的研究中，租金控制会导致<strong>不受控制的住所的租金更高</strong>。实行租金上限加剧了住房短缺问题。因此，等待的队列变得更长，将会成为租户，必须花更多的时间寻找住宅…</p><p>同样，租金控制对<strong>新的住宅建筑和供应</strong>的影响似乎是相似的。大约三分之二的研究表明了负面影响，而几项研究发现没有统计学上的显着影响……[v]租金控制政策的设计可能很重要……[n]可以免除构造的住房，因此仍然可以保持不受租金控制法规的影响…</p><p>对于租金管制对住房质量的影响，已发表的研究几乎一致。除<a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1051137724000020?via%3Dihub#bib0064">Gilderbloom（1986）</a>和<a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1051137724000020?via%3Dihub#bib0066">Gilderbloom和Markham（1996）</a>外，所有研究都表明，租金控制导致受法规约束的住宅<strong>质量的恶化</strong>。</p></blockquote><p>因此，虽然租金管制为那些有幸居住在租金管制单位的人们提供了很多好处，但它导致整体住房存量变得更小、更破旧。这会伤害那些不在租金控制的单位中的人，无论是通过提高租金和使他们难以找到搬家的地方而难以通过。</p><p>这并不意味着租金管制永远不值得付出代价。但这意味着有代价，主张租金管制的人需要考虑一下。</p><h4> 5. 如今服务成本增长缓慢</h4><p>还记得那张图表显示医疗保健和教育等服务在美国变得越来越难以负担吗？ </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9f471fa-37c8-494f-b123-f4a2c02c3c65_900x785.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9f471fa-37c8-494f-b123-f4a2c02c3c65_900x785.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9f471fa-37c8-494f-b123-f4a2c02c3c65_900x785.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9f471fa-37c8-494f-b123-f4a2c02c3c65_900x785.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9f471fa-37c8-494f-b123-f4a2c02c3c65_900x785.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9f471fa-37c8-494f-b123-f4a2c02c3c65_900x785.jpeg" width="900" height="785" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/a9f471fa-37c8-494f-b123-f4a2c02c3c65_900x785.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:785,&quot;width&quot;:900,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:176711,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9f471fa-37c8-494f-b123-f4a2c02c3c65_900x785.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9f471fa-37c8-494f-b123-f4a2c02c3c65_900x785.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9f471fa-37c8-494f-b123-f4a2c02c3c65_900x785.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa9f471fa-37c8-494f-b123-f4a2c02c3c65_900x785.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：<a href="https://x.com/Mark_J_Perry/status/1747995005518516419">马克·佩里</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>这通常是一个非常好的图表。这不是一个<em>完美的</em>图表——它夸大了大学费用，因为它忽略了经济援助，而且它的数据来源可能低估了 <a href="https://research.collegeboard.org/media/pdf/trends-college-pricing-presentation-2022.pdf">最近学费的下降</a>。此外，它还使住房出现亏损，因为住房价格在绝对意义上上涨，尽管工资上涨更多。但这些都是小问题——总体而言，该图表准确地传达了这样一个事实：自世纪之交以来，尽管许多实物商品变得更加便宜，但大件服务的价格却变得越来越便宜。</p><p>但是，当您制作这样的“百分比增长”图表时，您选择的起始年份非常重要。如果改变起始年份，趋势通常看起来会非常不同。正如杰里米·霍雷德（Jeremy Horpedahl）<a href="https://x.com/jmhorp/status/1750622296283189542">指出的</a>那样，自2000年以来，自2013年以来的许多大型服务实际上变得更加<em>负担得起</em>： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F799ba5c6-f311-4746-87f8-95f86376db2b_900x654.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F799ba5c6-f311-4746-87f8-95f86376db2b_900x654.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F799ba5c6-f311-4746-87f8-95f86376db2b_900x654.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F799ba5c6-f311-4746-87f8-95f86376db2b_900x654.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F799ba5c6-f311-4746-87f8-95f86376db2b_900x654.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F799ba5c6-f311-4746-87f8-95f86376db2b_900x654.jpeg" width="696" height="505.76" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s