div><p>医院服务是这里的一个大异常，但总体而言，医疗保健已经变得更加便宜，大学、日托和住房也是如此。这真是个好消息。它充满了希望，几十年来的大量服务成本增加是一种一次性现象，不会重复。</p><p>当然，这并不能改变这样一个事实：我们应该寻找方法让医疗保健、教育和住房变得更便宜。但这意味着阻止我们这样做的阻力现在可能已经减弱。这是一个重要的提醒：经济趋势并不是一成不变的。 </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?"><span>现在订阅</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/at-least-five-interesting-things-8ba?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/at-least-five-interesting-things-8ba?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>分享</span></a></p>; 
Three holes in the U.S.' economic strategy against ChinaLegacy chips, drones, and coordination with allies. https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/three-holes-holes-in-the-us-cormonic-strategy https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/three-holes-holes-in-the-us-cormonic-strategyNoah Smith Tue, 11 Jun 2024 00:21:41 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F475795ee-217c-4d8d-ac42-9976d60094c2_993x663.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F475795ee-217c-4d8d-ac42-9976d60094c2_993x663.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F475795ee-217c-4d8d-ac42-9976d60094c2_993x663.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F475795ee-217c-4d8d-ac42-9976d60094c2_993x663.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F475795ee-217c-4d8d-ac42-9976d60094c2_993x663.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F475795ee-217c-4d8d-ac42-9976d60094c2_993x663.jpeg" width="696" height="464.7009063444109" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/475795ee-217c-4d8d-ac42-9976d60094c2_993x663.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:663,&quot;width&quot;:993,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:696,&quot;bytes&quot;:68429,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F475795ee-217c-4d8d-ac42-9976d60094c2_993x663.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F475795ee-217c-4d8d-ac42-9976d60094c2_993x663.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F475795ee-217c-4d8d-ac42-9976d60094c2_993x663.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F475795ee-217c-4d8d-ac42-9976d60094c2_993x663.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line><figcaption class="image-caption">图片由<a href="https://unsplash.com/@elimendeinagella?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Elimende Inagella</a>在<a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/grayscale-photo-of-round-metal-frame-zx7VUt9txos?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Unsplash</a>上</figcaption></figure></div><p>现在写这篇文章几乎感觉有点毫无意义。在选举日之前，拜登政府在对华问题上不会做太多事情，如果特朗普获胜，所有对华政策的赌注都将大打折扣。但我认为无论如何将这些想法纳入一般讨论是件好事。</p><p>美国经济政策的转变<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/in-which-british-writers-scold-america">与中国有关</a>，这一切都与国防竞争有关。正如<a href="https://www.wsj.com/economy/the-u-s-finally-has-a-strategy-to-compete-with-china-will-it-work-ce4ea6cf">叶格雷格（Greg Ip）所写</a>，新范式由三部分组成——产业政策、出口管制和关税。关税保护美国的军事工业免受中国出口突然浪潮的破坏，产业政策增强了美国的军事工业，而出口管制则减缓了中国军事工业的发展。这些政策也有其他好处 - 脱碳，创造就业，技术进步等 - 但最终是中国与发达民主国家之间的防御平衡，从根本上讲是在这里驱动了一切的一切。</p><p>从总体框架来看，拜登政府的三大支柱还不错。工业政策尚未得到证明，如果滥用滥用，关税很容易适得其反，并且出口控制仍然包含许多漏洞。但总的来说，这是一种合理的方法。</p><p>但这还不够。在新的政策方法中，至少可以识别出至少剩余的三个漏洞非常容易。正如IP所写的那样，“第四回合，与盟友的统一经济阵线，仍然没有实现。”与此同时，如果最终产品是在中国境外组装的，关税就不容易针对中国零部件。尽管芯片和电池行业的产业政策很重要，但美国仍然忽视无人机。</p><h4>阻止中国“传统”芯片为一切提供动力</h4><p>美国对中国的出口控制旨在防止中国主导制造先进的尖端半导体。几乎没有希望<em>停止</em>中国在芯片制造中的进步，但希望是放慢他们的进步，以至于美国及其盟友可以保持领先地位。这就是为什么出口控制和其他一些限制的原因是考虑到“ <a href="https://georgetownsecuritystudiesreview.org/2023/12/26/u-s-economic-restrictions-on-china-small-yard-high-fence/">小院子，高栅栏</a>”的方法。</p><p>但是大量的计算机芯片<em>不是</em>前沿的。它们是“遗产”，“拖尾边缘”或“基础”芯片（三个含义相同的术语）。它们是较旧的技术，可以简单地制作 - 中国已经知道如何制造它们，并且拥有使它们大量的工具。出口控制几乎没有希望阻碍中国制造遗产筹码的进步。</p><p>但是，仅仅因为传统筹码在技术上不那么复杂并不能使它们变得不那么重要。正如<a href="https://rhg.com/research/thin-ice-us-pathways-to-regulating-china-sourced-legacy-chips/">Rhodium Group所指出的</a>那样，这些芯片在我们经济中的大部分事情都掌握了：</p><blockquote><p>传统筹码无处不在，因此必不可少。几乎所有电子设备（包括汽车，飞机和战斗机，医疗设备，智能手机，计算机以及农业和工业设备）与成熟的节点芯片和领先处理器一起提供动力。与大流行有关的限制驱使回家如何缺少单个芯片，如何支撑整个制造装配线，使消费者难以置信地说，他们的新车可以被剥夺通常是理所当然的功能，例如座位会加热并自动调整。</p></blockquote><p>目前，这些芯片中的大多数仍在中国以外制造，但中国正在赶上赛车，建造了绝对巨大的新工厂： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F16484902-0613-4b9a-804d-00a07fe3609f_1620x1635.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F16484902-0613-4b9a-804d-00a07fe3609f_1620x1635.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F16484902-0613-4b9a-804d-00a07fe3609f_1620x1635.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F16484902-0613-4b9a-804d-00a07fe3609f_1620x1635.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F16484902-0613-4b9a-804d-00a07fe3609f_1620x1635.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F16484902-0613-4b9a-804d-00a07fe3609f_1620x1635.jpeg" width="706" height="712.3035714285714" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/16484902-0613-4b9a-804d-00a07fe3609f_1620x1635.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1469,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:706,&quot;bytes&quot;:436430,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F16484902-0613-4b9a-804d-00a07fe3609f_1620x1635.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F16484902-0613-4b9a-804d-00a07fe3609f_1620x1635.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F16484902-0613-4b9a-804d-00a07fe3609f_1620x1635.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F16484902-0613-4b9a-804d-00a07fe3609f_1620x1635.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://rhg.com/research/thin-ice-us-pathways-to-regulating-china-sourced-legacy-chips/">若想符</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>这种新能力的大部分将在中国用于中国消费者的产品。但是其中的大部分将被出口 - 要么直接或嵌入其他中国制造的产品（例如汽车和电子产品）中。正如我们在汽车和电池中看到的那样，一旦中国改建了其工业机器并开始用补贴为行业淋浴，那么其他发达国家的公司在面对猛烈袭击的情况下可能很难生存。传统筹码是中国<a href="https://csis-website-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/s3fs-public/publication/220523_DiPippo_Red_Ink.pdf?VersionId=LH8ILLKWz4o.bjrwNS7csuX_C04FyEre">最严重的补贴</a>行业之一。</p><p>这可能会损害美国及其盟友的几种方式。</p><p>首先，来自中国传统筹码行业的竞争可能会淹没和破坏美国及其盟友的许多芯片行业 - 日本，韩国，台湾和欧洲以及印度的新生芯片行业。这将使供应连锁店在战争时处于危险之中。</p><p>这也将剥夺中国以外的芯片制造商的收入来资助领先的筹码的发展，从而使他们更依赖政府补贴。破坏TSMC，Intel和Samsung等公司的传统筹码业务可能是中国对出口控制的答案。</p><p>最后，还有网络安全角度。有些人担心中国制造的旧筹码可能会带有内置的后门，这会使中国的军队可以监视美国人，禁用美国基础设施，将一堆美国设备和消费品变成砖块，甚至控制着车辆，甚至崩溃他们。</p><p>因此，有很多理由试图阻止中国成为为其他所有人制造传统筹码的国家。但是如何做呢？ Rhodium Group <a href="https://rhg.com/research/thin-ice-us-pathways-to-regulating-china-sourced-legacy-chips/">建议包括关税在内的各种类型的贸易壁垒</a>将中国筹码拒之门外。拜登<a href="https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/statements-releases/2024/05/14/fact-sheet-president-biden-takes-action-to-protect-american-workers-and-businesses-from-chinas-unfair-trade-practices/">最近的一轮关税</a>中包括中国筹码。</p><p>但是，您无法对您甚至看不到该国的东西征收关税。目前，美国政府的进口筹码来自哪里。如果墨西哥的汽车或泰国制造的笔记本电脑在其中有一个中国芯片，美国政府根本不知道。这意味着，尽管阻止中国芯片的进口很容易，但<em>很难</em>阻止含有中国芯片的产品的进口。</p><p>因此，第一个任务是<strong>获取有关美国进口中所有芯片的良好数据</strong>。目前，有关组件进口的数据仅来自经合组织<a href="https://www.nber.org/system/files/working_papers/w31820/w31820.pdf">的滞后几年</a>，即使不是逐个产品和公司逐个公司的细分也没有提供。美国需要实施一个报告和检查制度，该制度为政府提供了有关该国的每个计算机芯片的良好，最新的信息。</p><p>数据显然是这里最重要的事情。但是，正如史蒂文·格林特（Steven Glinert）最近的<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/americas-semiconductor-policy-is">《诺阿普尼翁访客》（Noahpinion）帖子</a>中概述的那样，我们还可以采取一些其他政策步骤。这些包括a）对用于设计旧芯片的软件的导出限制，b）更多的筹码行动金钱或类似的遗产芯片制造商补贴。这两者都可能只有边际影响，但它们可能是贸易障碍的补充。</p><p>确实，数据是这里的关键。您无法与看不见的东西作斗争，目前，美国政府根本看不到中国筹码。我不知道目前或计划中的政府努力在美国进口中识别中国筹码。</p><h4>建立平民无人机行业</h4><p>美国工业政策，出口控制和关税针对战略行业 - 芯片，汽车，电池等。但是，到目前为止，似乎有一个非常重要的行业已经摆脱了这一努力：无人机。</p><p>到现在为止，许多作家<a href="https://www.technologyreview.com/2023/01/30/1067348/mass-market-military-drones-have-changed-the-way-wars-are-fought/">指出</a>，无人机已经成为现代战争至关重要的。在乌克兰，大量无人机用于侦察，炮兵针对，摧毁敌方车辆，甚至直接杀死敌方人员。如果您能忍受它，我建议您在乌克兰战场上观看一架小型玩具无人驾驶飞机<a href="https://x.com/JHartley2/status/1749495155915141203">，并杀死一名俄罗斯士兵</a>。那架无人机是由人类远程驾驶的，但是在不太遥远的未来，无人机将是自动<a href="https://www.politico.eu/article/robots-coming-ukraine-testing-ground-ai-artificial-intelligence-powered-combat-war-russia/">AI驱动的杀戮机器</a>。到那时，这是一个悬而未决的问题，即人类士兵是否能够在战争的前线生存。</p><p>基本上，有两种方法可以为无人机供电：内燃机和电动机。由内燃机提供动力的无人机往往更大，更重，更快，更强大。但是电动无人机往往会便宜得多，并且可以以较高的体积制造。一架沙赫无人机，是最小，最便宜的内燃无人机之一，价格<a href="https://www.twz.com/news-features/what-does-a-shahed-136-really-cost">在20,000美元至375,000美元之间</a>。相比之下，DJI Mavic 3的价格<a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=mavic+3&amp;rlz=1C1RXQR_enUS1011US1011&amp;oq=mavic+3&amp;gs_&amp;sourceid=chrome&amp;ie=UTF-8">约为2,000美元</a>，而Matrice 300的价格<a href="https://store.dji.com/product/matrice-300-rtk-and-dji-care-plus?vid=111261">约为13,000美元</a>。两种类型的无人机在战场上都有其用途，这意味着任何无法建造或轻松捕获大量廉价的电动无人机的国家在战争中处于不利地位。</p><p>目前，中国公司在商业无人机的制造方面具有<a href="https://dronedj.com/2023/12/12/top-drone-manufacturer-ranking-2023/">压倒性的市场份额</a>，DJI是主要的参与者。第二大公司是美国的Skydio，但它们仍然远远远远落后于DJI，而且没有其他大型无人机制造商。这意味着像乌克兰这样的现代战场是由中国制造的产品主导的。这意味着，如果中国与美国及其盟友交战，后者将发现自己没有很多小型的电动无人机。</p><p>美国已<a href="https://theasymmetric.substack.com/p/missing-the-swarm-for-the-drones">考虑禁止</a>中国无人机，但据我所知，没有人在谈论建立美国<em>无人机</em>行业的工业政策。拜登政府似乎正在考虑无人机类似于导弹或炮弹类似，这是一种弹药而不是一种弹药，因此只有军队需要购买的东西。但是，在与中国的旷日持久的战争中，美国民用无人机行业将为美军提供重要的<em>激增能力</em>，就像第二次世界大战期间汽车制造商制造的坦克和飞机一样。</p><p>鼓励建立美国商业无人机行业的一种可能的工业政策是<em>放松管制</em>。 FAA已经大大<a href="https://www.planeandpilotmag.com/article/faa-deregulates-small-commercial-drones/">放松了有关小型商业无人机的法规</a>，但是允许无人机在视觉线之外操作（BVLOS）将有很大帮助，因为这是战争中使用无人机的方式。 BVLOS放松管制<a href="https://www.commercialuavnews.com/regulations/u-s-congress-set-to-mandate-faa-establish-uav-bvlos-final-rule">现在正在国会中进行</a>，但尚不清楚这些变化将会有多有意义。</p><p>但是，尽管您可以通过放松管制来鼓励无人机消耗，但最终，您实际上要购买无人机的消费者限制。有了电动汽车和计算机芯片，这一点却不再是一个问题，但是即使在中国，无人机也是一个利基市场。通常，制造商需要大型消费市场才能扩大并降低成本。那么中国公司如何变得如此擅长制造无人机？</p><p>格伦·卢克（Glenn Luk）在2018年有<a href="https://www.readwriteinvest.com/p/why-is-china-so-good-at-making-drones">一篇很棒的帖子</a>，他指出，用于制造<em>无人机的</em>大多数东西也用于制作<em>电话</em>。最大的例外是电动机本身，它与搅拌机或其他家用电器中的电动机更相似。</p><p>因此，在美国或精选的国家 /地区，美国对无人机的工业政策将仅需要激励制造无人机<em>组件</em>（电动机，显示器，相机等）。这将类似于《减少通货膨胀法》激励电池的国内制造的方式，而不是IRA激励电动汽车本身的制造方式。对这些组件将进入的消费产品的最终需求（手机，电器等）已经存在（实际上，其中一些需求已经由IRA提供了补贴）。</p><p>这种工业政策的成本几乎不及《 IRA或筹码法》，因为除芯片和电池以外的电子组件非常便宜。但是，这可以帮助恢复国内消费电子行业，如果需要，可以快速将其重新定义为无人机行业。因此，尽管似乎没有人在谈论补贴电动机行业或展示行业，但这似乎是一个有用的漏洞。</p><h4>统一的阵线</h4><p>重要的是要记住中国比美国<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-war-economy-sizing-up-the-new">大的</a>人口是人口的四倍，并且是增值的两倍。尽管在某些技术领域，两国之间的任何旷日持久的冲突都将使美国保持不佳。换句话说，美国国家安全依赖于<em>联盟</em>至关重要 - 为了能够与更大的对手掌握，您需要一个帮派。</p><p>尽管美国擅长于军事联盟，但它并不那么擅长<em>经济</em>联盟。公平地说，没有人真正是 - 经济关系比国防合作要多得多，因此没有标准模板可以准确地应如何工作。但是，在一些领域，美国可以与盟友更紧密地合作，以建立能够匹配中国的跨国经济。</p><p>最明显的区域是<em>出口控制</em>。美国需要荷兰，日本，德国，韩国和台湾等国家<a href="https://thediplomat.com/2024/05/the-missing-links-in-us-chip-policy/">，以便合作，</a>如果有机会将尖端的芯片制作技术放在中国的手中。到目前为止，拜登政府在这方面做得很好。</p><p>其次，美国应立即在其所有盟友之间进行<strong>国防制造合作</strong>。美国枯萎的国防工业基地和缺乏商业造船业的手段将需要时间来解决；同时，美国应该严重依靠日本和韩国这样的合作伙伴，以使军事资源阻止中国。幸运的是，已经有<a href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Politics/International-relations/Indo-Pacific/Indo-Pacific-should-create-common-defense-market-Hudson-analyst-says">一些方向有一些动作</a>：</p><blockquote><p>美国及其在印度太平洋地区的盟友正在朝着为国防工业建立事实上的“共同市场”，建立相同的工业标准并加强了彼此的国防工业基础……最近在Aukus Partners中对出口管制的放松……为此……经济学家和国防分析师威廉·施耐德（William Schneider）说，建造核动力潜艇为更全区的国防行业合作创造了一个空缺。</p><p>施耐德说，特别是日本在该行业一级的国防合作中已经成熟，理由是该国的造船能能力。</p><p>五角大楼的收购和维持最高官员威廉·拉普兰特（William Laplante）将开始与日本同行会面……讨论合作。他将在东京举行的美国国防工业合作，收购和维持论坛的首届会议邀请美国和日本国防承包商的代表讨论武器的共同开发，生产和维护……</p><p>施耐德说：“副部长拉普兰特（Laplante）促进的一件事是联盟工业基础的概念。”</p></blockquote><p>美国所做的第二个领域是<em>贸易</em>。几个月前，我写了这篇文章： </p><div class="digest-post-embed" data-attrs="{&quot;nodeId&quot;:&quot;abbd77ef-236c-47bb-b4ee-1170e2005286&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;The paradigm shift in U.S. economic policy began during the 2016 presidential election campaign. It was in that campaign that the candidates of both parties agreed on scrapping the Trans-Pacific Partnership (TPP). The TPP was a proposed free trade deal between the U.S. and a bunch of friendly Asian countries that &#8230;&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;sm&quot;,&quot;isEditorNode&quot;:true,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;The U.S. would be insane to go it alone on trade and manufacturing&quot;,&quot;publishedBylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:8243895,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:&quot;Econ blogger&quot;,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/89fd964a-586f-461a-9f5a-ea4587d45728_397x441.png&quot;,&quot;is_guest&quot;:false,&quot;bestseller_tier&quot;:10000}],&quot;post_date&quot;:&quot;2024-04-05T01:06:01.900Z&quot;,&quot;cover_image&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F73951205-b7b7-429e-b5c4-ad6533882105_1024x1024.jpeg&quot;,&quot;cover_image_alt&quot;:null,&quot;canonical_url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-us-would-be-insane-to-go-it-alone&quot;,&quot;section_name&quot;:null,&quot;id&quot;:143282101,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;newsletter&quot;,&quot;reaction_count&quot;:253,&quot;comment_count&quot;:102,&quot;publication_name&quot;:&quot;Noahpinion&quot;,&quot;publication_logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04281755-2cd6-42e5-a496-e69153abebb2_281x281.png&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true}"></div><p>中国的战略公司 - 华为，比亚德和其他人都可以进入一个巨大的市场。从<a href="https://www.economist.com/finance-and-economics/2024/06/06/why-global-gdp-might-be-7trn-bigger-than-everyone-thought">某些措施</a>来看，该市场甚至比美国更大，但美国，欧洲，日本，韩国等将是一个<em>更大的</em>组合市场。统一这些市场将使美国和盟友公司 - 英特尔，波音，三星，丰田，空中客车，特斯拉，现代等 - 有能力扩展更多并降低成本。如果添加印度，该集团将更大，更强大。</p><p>因此，在某种程度上，美国可以将其联盟分成一个<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bidens-trade-challenge-kicking-the-china-dependency-habit-dfdb3a0">统一的交易集团</a>。但是，面临的挑战是，大多数其他国家不愿意将中国脱离供应链。如果该街区的其他成员只是充当中国商品的导管，那么锻造反中国经济集团就毫无用处。拜登政府已<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/article/2024/may/21/janet-yellen-eu-us-chinese-exports-tariffs-electric-vehicles">努力</a>使其他国家达成拜登的关税，但是这些努力不可避免地会非常稀疏和可疑的效率。</p><p>这里的一个想法是奖励盟国进入美国市场的战略性重要的公司，以换取与美国的中国贸易政策协调的。这些公司将有效地选择 - 与美国开展业务或与中国开展业务。同时，美国可以要求盟友在战略行业中为自己的公司提供类似的交易。</p><p>另外，如果美国能够在整个供应链中获取有关组件采购的良好数据，那么它可以与所有盟友签订自由贸易协定，然后征税中文组成部分。但这将需要a）a）对进口组件的更好数据收集，b）美国公众同意所谓的“贸易协议”。两党十字军以使TPP沉没后，后者的前景看起来很昏暗。因此，这里真正的诀窍是在不引发贸易保护主义反对的情况下获得交易联盟的好处。</p><p>不过，总的来说，我认为对经济联盟的言辞以及与盟友交易与与敌人交易之间的差异将有助于为美国公众做好上述所有政策的准备。美国面临的竞争对手比我们曾经面临过的任何人都更大，更强大，而且我们无法独自去。这是我不希望特朗普或他的追随者会接受的信息，这就是为什么民主党人需要站起来并在这里领导的原因。 </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?"><span>现在订阅</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/three-holes-in-the-us-economic-strategy?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/three-holes-in-the-us-economic-strategy?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>分享</span></a></p><p></p><p></p>; 
Decade of the BatteryA repost with some updates. https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/decade-of-the-battery-334 https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/decade-of-the-battery-334Noah Smith Sun, 09 Jun 2024 06:59:56 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae0f0dbd-6aa7-4197-99bd-cc89f5c4f27f_1183x790.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae0f0dbd-6aa7-4197-99bd-cc89f5c4f27f_1183x790.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae0f0dbd-6aa7-4197-99bd-cc89f5c4f27f_1183x790.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae0f0dbd-6aa7-4197-99bd-cc89f5c4f27f_1183x790.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae0f0dbd-6aa7-4197-99bd-cc89f5c4f27f_1183x790.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae0f0dbd-6aa7-4197-99bd-cc89f5c4f27f_1183x790.jpeg" width="1183" height="790" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ae0f0dbd-6aa7-4197-99bd-cc89f5c4f27f_1183x790.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:790,&quot;width&quot;:1183,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:33845,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae0f0dbd-6aa7-4197-99bd-cc89f5c4f27f_1183x790.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae0f0dbd-6aa7-4197-99bd-cc89f5c4f27f_1183x790.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae0f0dbd-6aa7-4197-99bd-cc89f5c4f27f_1183x790.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fae0f0dbd-6aa7-4197-99bd-cc89f5c4f27f_1183x790.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line><figcaption class="image-caption">图片由<a href="https://unsplash.com/@asoggetti?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Alessio Soggetti</a>在<a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/turned-on-drone-rSFxBGpnluw?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Unsplash</a>上</figcaption></figure></div><p><em>在2022年，<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/decade-of-the-battery">我写了一篇文章</a>，认为电池将是2020年代的定义技术。那是在chatgpt发行和生成AI的繁荣的几个月之前。鉴于突然的流出，谦虚的电池似乎古朴而平淡，我的帖子似乎令人难以置信。</em></p><p><em>然而两年后，我认为我的帖子仍然坚持。这两年已经看到，小型电池供电的无人机完全改变了<a href="https://www.technologyreview.com/2023/01/30/1067348/mass-market-military-drones-have-changed-the-way-wars-are-fought/">战争的方式</a>。 They have seen battery storage become a common complement to solar, <a href="https://x.com/drvolts/status/1793743067645972773">solving almost all</a> of solar&#39;s intermittency problem and drawing huge amounts of investment worldwide. Batteries have powered the sudden meteoric rise of <a href="https://www.technologyreview.com/2023/02/21/1068880/how-did-china-dominate-electric-cars-policy/">China&#39;s car industry</a> , which went from an also-ran to a juggernaut that suddenly threatens to dominate the entire global auto market. AI is certainly magical and holds incredible potential, but in just a couple of years, batteries have begun to transform human energy supply, war, transportation, and geopolitical dominance.</em></p><p> <em>Also, it&#39;s quickly becoming apparent that AI and batteries are, in many ways, perfectly complementary technologies. Drones are human-piloted now, but <a href="https://www.wsj.com/tech/drone-swarms-are-about-to-change-the-balance-of-military-power-e091aa6f">autonomous AI-operated drone swarms</a> are coming, and they are going to change war and the balance of power yet again. AI promises to turn robotics from a niche type of machine tool into <a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/techno-optimism-for-2024">a ubiquitous feature of our world</a> . The rise of autonomous machines will be — must be — battery-powered.</em></p><p> <em>So here&#39;s my post from 2022. See how well you think it still holds up.</em></p><div><hr></div><p> In 2015, Benedict Evans wrote a very influential piece called “ <a href="https://twitter.com/benedictevans/status/627884650300506113">The smartphone is the new sun</a> ”. By the middle of the 2010s, it was pretty clear that that decade would be defined in many ways by the mobile computing platform that Steve Jobs unveiled in 2007. For regular people, smartphones became the locus of their lives — an ever-present tether constantly connecting them to the digital world and allowing them to navigate the physical one. For industry, smartphones and the applications they enabled became a massive opportunity for investment and profit.</p><p> Now, however, it seems like we might be reaching the end of that rainbow. The basic reason is that with smartphones, IT companies have now harvested essentially all of people&#39;s surplus attention and time. <a href="https://www.pewresearch.org/internet/2022/08/10/teens-social-media-and-technology-2022/">A new Pew survey of teens&#39; social media habits</a> found that almost half of young people are online “almost constantly”, up from a quarter in the mid-2010s. And <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_countries_by_smartphone_penetration">smartphone penetration</a> in rich countries is around 80%. So it&#39;s natural for both consumers and investors/entrepreneurs to be looking around for what technologies might enable another Cambrian explosion of innovation in the next decade.</p><p> Many people think that this technology is going to be machine learning/AI. But although I do think ML will indeed be very important, I&#39;m going to make an argument that the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General-purpose_technology">general-purpose technology</a> that will really transform our society is the battery.</p><p> This is interesting because it&#39;s a bit of a swerve from the pattern of the last four decades. From 1980-2020, the innovations that reshaped our world were all in information technology — the PC, the internet, the smartphone and the social network. But batteries are an “atoms” technology — something that powers our physical world instead of helping us spin a new digital one. So the Decade of the Battery will look more like earlier decades, in which physical appliances like washing machines, refrigerators, and air conditioning <a href="https://ourworldindata.org/technology-adoption">were the hot new thing</a> . </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7dc6442b-7b87-4254-b943-5d9e1d963de3_3400x2400.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7dc6442b-7b87-4254-b943-5d9e1d963de3_3400x2400.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7dc6442b-7b87-4254-b943-5d9e1d963de3_3400x2400.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7dc6442b-7b87-4254-b943-5d9e1d963de3_3400x2400.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7dc6442b-7b87-4254-b943-5d9e1d963de3_3400x2400.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7dc6442b-7b87-4254-b943-5d9e1d963de3_3400x2400.png" width="1456" height="1028" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7dc6442b-7b87-4254-b943-5d9e1d963de3_3400x2400.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscre